Synopsis:
   set status_query [<text>]

Description:
   This variable sets the string displayed in the status bar when the client
   is querying another user.  If there is no query active, nothing is shown.

   This string is represented as %Q in the STATUS_FORMAT string.  It will
   expand to the nickname being queried when used in STATUS_QUERY.

Examples:
   Customizing the string indicating an active query:
      /set status_query Querying %Q

See Also:
   query(1); set(4) status_format

